<br>
I ran a server with the rest of my guildmates for some time when NWN released. When NWN initially released good lord was it buggy. I've got alot of fond memories from NWN, but the game just was not done as it should have been in my opinion. I remember Bioware stating flat out when Vampire the Masquerade: Redemption came out, how they said they were so dissapointed with the way the NOD engine worked. It was at that time they stated that they were going to make sure there was no coding involved in the aurora toolset. Its another classic case of promises made and the delivery didn't happen. Not their fault however, because of the intervention of Atari. Atari has been in hot water for a while fiscaly speaking as is. The only reason they even got involved with the Horizons MMORPG is because they thought it would be a way for them to generate some cash to help their debt issues.<br>
<br>
Sure you've seen a design doc, I believe you. But from what I know, you've seen the design doc that was released to the public for the content that was released. Do you really honestly believe that they would release a product to the public unfinished and give you a design doc for stuff thats not present? Bioware isn't foolish. They are a business like anyone else out there.<br>
<br>
NWN does have alot of good points, I still play it here or there myself, and I am looking forward to both expansions. But, I think for its online counterpart, it leaves alot to be desired. I just am not fond of the 3e rules for one. I just feel as a gamer they push the envelope too much.<br>
<br>
I see lots of people love the servers, hey thats great. If you like it, play it and have fun. But I personally do not like most of the PW servers. I find them pretty dull overall, and they just feel too far removed from that table top feel. I don't feel the creativity or ingenuity is really present that drives home that feel of a table in a multi player setting. Overall the impression I have recieved was more of an attempt at turning it into an MMORPG and not an RPG.<br>
<br>
I'm well aware of City of Doors, and yes its good stuff. I have a dislike for alot of the stuff that I see on NW Vault, especially the modules. However there are some good things out there. If you haven't played the Twilight module, its a damn fine creative piece. Professionaly done in my opinion. I enjoyed it as much, maybe a little better then the NWN campaign.<br>
<br>
No one agrees on everything all the time. You like NWN, I could take it or leave it. No big deal, if everyone agreed on everything all the time the world would be a boring place. <p>Banegrivm Shadowblight<br>
