Ok we may all go, Ewww, Turbine did AC(Which was not a bad game, very stable), and AC2 which I have never played but hear its all buggy, and still is. Now you may all wanna say Turbine did this blah, blah, blah, evil, blah, blah, etc.....Well your right Turbine made this game, and it sucks I guess. BUT, yes there is a but, Turbine was working with big bad Microsoft looming over its shoulders and Turbine had to do all Microsoft told them. Why you ask. Well Turbine is like Spiderman in the sense that they are strong and agile and deliver what they set out to do, and Microsoft is like the Hulk, as in they tell Turbine what they want or else Hulk Smash!<br>
<br>
Turbine gave Microsoft exactly what they wanted in AC, and AC2. What this did was give Turbine a nice payoff from Microsoft so they could go onto other projects and get the hell away from mister Micro. So now they are doing Lord of the Rings Online, and Dungeons and Dragons online. They have skills, and yes they will make mistakes. But they also know this is not some hack game world like AC, or EQ. This is D&amp;D, the grandaddy. The one that started it all. And depending on what game setting they chose to place it in they will have a huge workload, and a HUGE fanbase to impress. <br>
<br>
